<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12046k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12046k">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12046k"> 46(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Men burnt in mannequin / d&apos;osier ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les druides de chaque cit&eacute; exercent sans aucun doute leur pouvoir, de fa&ccedil;on constante, &agrave; l&apos;int&eacute;rieur de leur peuple. Mais, de toute la Gaule, ils se r&eacute;unissent chaque ann&eacute;e &agrave; l&apos;ombilic de la nation, dans une for&ecirc;t du territoire des Carnutes (r&eacute;gion d&apos;Orl&eacute;ans). C&apos;est l&agrave; qu&apos;ils d&eacute;cident des affaires communes du pays. A l&apos;issue de ces assembl&eacute;es, g&eacute;n&eacute;rales ou locales, le juge se retrouve pr&ecirc;tre. Il accomplit, pour le salut de la cit&eacute; ou de la nation les sacrifices solennels. D&apos;immenses mannequins <font color="green">[wickerwork figure]</font> d&apos;osier sont remplis d&apos;hommes vivants, de criminels de pr&eacute;f&eacute;rence, mais, &agrave; leur d&eacute;faut, d&apos;innocents. Le feu consume le tout. <br> [Undoubtedly the druids of each city wielded their power, in a constant fashion, among their people. But from all over Gaul they gathered each year at the nation&apos;s navel in the forest of the land of the Carnutes (in the environs of Orl&eacute;ans). It is there that they decided the common business of the land. After these meetings, general or local, the judge became priest again. For the health of the city or the nation he made solemn sacrifices. <mark>Immense wicker mannequins were filled with live men</mark>, preferably criminals, but when they did not have any, innocent people. The <mark>fire killed them all.</mark> <small> Albert Grenier, <a name="AGLG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AGLG"><cite title="source">Les Gaulois</cite></a> (1923) 125</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
